<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-09-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-09-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">841.857 Athenia/1: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-outside-research" calendar="gregorian" when="1939-09-03">[undated]</date>.<lb/>[Received September 3, 1939—8:50
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Foreign Office has just telephoned that it is releasing to press
                                report SS <hi rend="italic">Athenia</hi> of Donaldson Line torpedoed
                                200 miles off Malin Head with 1400 passengers aboard. S. O. S.
                                received. Ship sinking fast.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kennedy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>